## Installation

Run all these commands in sequence:

```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/golang-fiber-chat.git
cd golang-fiber-chat

# 2. Install Go dependencies
go mod tidy

# 3. Setup PostgreSQL database
# Run these SQL commands in your PostgreSQL client
CREATE DATABASE chat_app;

-- Users table
CREATE TABLE users (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  password_hash TEXT NOT NULL
);

-- Messages table
CREATE TABLE messages (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  sender VARCHAR(50),
  recipient VARCHAR(50),
  content TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

# 4. Configure environment variables
# Create a .env file in project root
# Example:
# PORT=5000
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://username:password@localhost:5432/chat_app
# JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret_key

# 5. Run the server
go run main.go
